# E2E Testing Standards

E2E tests verify complete user flows in a real browser. They test what users actually see and do.

## Location

- `tv-guide-app/e2e/<flow>.spec.ts`
- Group by user flow: `onboarding.spec.ts`, `guide-navigation.spec.ts`, `settings.spec.ts`

## Runner

Playwright targeting the web build (`npx playwright test`).

## Selectors — Always Use `data-testid`

**Every interactive or assertable element must have a `data-testid` attribute.** Never select by class name, tag name, or text content alone.

```tsx
// In component code
<Pressable data-testid="sport-filter-nba" onPress={...}>
  <Text>NBA</Text>
</Pressable>

<View data-testid="event-card-123">
  <Text data-testid="event-card-123-home-team">Lakers</Text>
  <Text data-testid="event-card-123-score">108</Text>
</View>
```

```typescript
// In test code
await page.getByTestId('sport-filter-nba').click();
await expect(page.getByTestId('event-card-123-home-team')).toHaveText('Lakers');
```

### `data-testid` Naming Convention

- Kebab-case: `event-card`, `sport-filter-nba`, `service-picker-modal`
- Hierarchical: `<parent>-<child>` for nested elements
- Include dynamic IDs when needed: `event-card-${event.id}`
- Prefix by component: `onboarding-get-started`, `settings-service-youtube-tv`

### When to Add `data-testid`

Add to any element that an E2E test might need to:
- **Click:** buttons, links, filter pills, service toggles
- **Assert text:** team names, scores, times, section headers
- **Assert visibility:** modals, empty states, loading indicators
- **Assert count:** event cards in a section, services in a list

## Test Structure

```typescript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test.describe('Guide Navigation', () => {
  test.beforeEach(async ({ page }) => {
    await page.goto('http://localhost:8081');
    // Complete onboarding if needed
  });

  test('filters events when sport pill is tapped', async ({ page }) => {
    await page.getByTestId('sport-filter-nba').click();
    await expect(page.getByTestId('section-header')).toContainText('NBA');
    await expect(page.getByTestId('event-card').first()).toBeVisible();
  });
});
```

## Key Principles

### Test user behavior, not implementation
- Click what a user would click
- Assert what a user would see
- Don't assert internal state, Redux stores, or network requests

### Each test is independent
- Never depend on another test running first
- Use `beforeEach` to set up a clean state
- Complete onboarding programmatically if the test doesn't test onboarding

### Wait for the app, don't use arbitrary sleeps
- Use Playwright auto-waiting (built into actions like `click`, `toBeVisible`)
- Use `waitForSelector` or `waitForResponse` for dynamic content
- **Never use `page.waitForTimeout()`** — it's fragile and slow. Instead:
  - Wait for a specific element: `await expect(locator).toBeVisible({ timeout: 10_000 })`
  - Wait for navigation: `await page.waitForURL('**/guide')`
  - Wait for network: `await page.waitForResponse('**/api/events')`
  - Wait for loading to finish: `await expect(page.getByTestId('loading')).not.toBeVisible()`

### Handle async data loading
- Wait for the loading state to resolve before asserting
- Use `await expect(locator).toBeVisible({ timeout: 10_000 })` for API-dependent content
- For content that depends on a live API, assert that either events OR an empty state appears — never assert a specific event title from production data

## Page Object Pattern (optional but recommended)

For complex flows, extract page interactions:

```typescript
class GuidePage {
  constructor(private page: Page) {}

  async filterBySport(sport: string) {
    await this.page.getByTestId(`sport-filter-${sport}`).click();
  }

  async getEventCards() {
    return this.page.getByTestId(/^event-card-/).all();
  }

  async expectSectionVisible(name: string) {
    await expect(this.page.getByTestId(`section-${name}`)).toBeVisible();
  }
}
```

## What to Cover

### Onboarding flow
- Welcome screen renders
- Service picker allows selection/deselection
- Completing onboarding navigates to guide

### Guide screen
- Events load and display
- Sport filter pills change displayed events
- Time sections appear (Live Now, Starting Soon, Later Today, Tomorrow)
- Event cards show team names, time, and service badges

### Settings
- Service toggles persist
- Toggling a service updates the guide

### Service picker modal
- Opens when an event has multiple services
- Shows correct service options
- Closes on cancel

## Assertions

- `toBeVisible()` — element is in the DOM and visible
- `toHaveText('exact')` — exact text match
- `toContainText('partial')` — contains substring
- `toHaveCount(n)` — number of matching elements
- Never assert on CSS classes or computed styles

## False Positive Prevention

- **Never assert only `toBeVisible()` on a container.** If the container always renders (even when empty), the test always passes. Assert on meaningful content inside it.
- **Never assert on text that comes from `localStorage` setup in `beforeEach`.** That tests your setup, not the app. Assert on behavior that results from the app reading and rendering that data.
- **Test the negative case too.** If you test "selecting NBA filter shows NBA events," also test "selecting NBA filter hides NFL events" — otherwise the filter might be broken and showing everything.
- **Avoid `hasEvents || hasEmpty` catch-all assertions.** These pass regardless of what the app shows. Pick one expected state and assert it specifically, or split into separate tests.

## CI Considerations

- Tests run on headless Chromium in Ubuntu — no GPU acceleration, slower than local
- The Expo web server takes 30-60s to bundle on first request; `playwright.config.ts` has a 120s `webServer.timeout` to accommodate this
- `retries: 2` in CI catches genuine timing flakes, but if a test needs retries consistently, fix the root cause
- On failure, the Playwright HTML report is uploaded as a GitHub Actions artifact with screenshots and traces

## Running

```bash
cd tv-guide-app && npx playwright test           # all E2E tests
cd tv-guide-app && npx playwright test --ui       # interactive mode
cd tv-guide-app && npx playwright test <file>     # single file
```
